<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-84-1302 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper presents a brief outlook on the electrical industry and itspolicies relating to polychlorinated biphenyls and the public. In Canadathere is a need for industry efforts to inform the public about the natureof PCBs, and to provide accurate and effective public relations in thecase of PCB-related accidents that result in environmental contamination,in order to ensure that any hazards to the public are not exaggeratedor overestimated.</TEXT></DOC>